	abstract = {Background:‚ÄÇ Recent advances in wearable sensor technologies enable objective and long-term monitoring of motor activities in a patient‚Äôs habitual environment. People with mobility impairments require appropriate data processing algorithms that deal with their altered movement patterns and determine clinically meaningful outcome measures. Over the years, a large variety of algorithms have been published and this review provides an overview of their outcome measures, the concepts of the algorithms, the type and placement of required sensors as well as the investigated patient populations and measurement properties.
